Overview

This project simulates a laser-based communication system for satellite data transmission using MATLAB. An image is converted into a train of laser pulses and transmitted to a satellite. The satellite modulates these pulses using External Amplitude Modulation (EAM) and sends them back to the receiver. The receiver processes the pulses and reconstructs the original image using MATLAB signal and image processing techniques.

This demonstrates a secure, high-speed optical communication method for space systems.

Key Features

✨ Image-to-laser pulse conversion
✨ External Amplitude Modulation (EAM) simulation
✨ MATLAB-based signal processing
✨ Image reconstruction at receiver
✨ Demonstration of optical satellite communication

