How It Works

An input image is loaded into MATLAB.

Pixel values are converted into a binary data stream.

The binary stream is converted into laser pulse signals.

The pulses are modulated using External Amplitude Modulation (EAM).

The modulated signal is transmitted through a simulated communication channel.

The receiver detects the pulses and reconstructs the original image using decoding algorithms.

